[6]. Like other block codes, LDPC code is represented by a parity-check matrix H (mn) which has low density of 1’s as in (1). The generator matrix G(k  n) is generated from H matrix, where k m  n is the length of information. Regular LDPC codes consist of exactly wc 1’s in each column and exactly wr  wc (n / m) 1’s in each row. The code rate R  k / n is related to these parameters via R 1 (wc / wr ) . An example of H matrix (5, 10) with wc  2 and wr  4 is shown in equation (1):

